<plot>Bruno was about to lose control of his life. On Millenium night, with his friends, he tried unsuccessfully to obtain the answers to his questions about death and after-death, the meaning of life, or the reasons to live. Until he heard about the millenial hindu tradition "akasha" with its division of the universe into dimensions between space and movement, the word expresses not only the physical dimensions of space, our space, but also multiple spiritual dimensions of alternative spaces, where there's no limit you are truly free. A bizarre and mystic incursion in the eastern secrets of mind.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?027543</url></doc>
